    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public void execute()
        In this method the relationshipConstrain(cyclic,total,irreflexive, acyclic, reflexive) is created/ invoked into the model tree through setting it's parameter. After that when a relationshipConstrain already exist beside the relationshipConstrain to be invoked all Bendpoints from this relationshipConstrain are added to the created relationshipConstrain as well. When more as one Relation exists between the target and the source of the relationshipConstrain than a Bendpoint is added to the created relationshipConstrain to make the relationshipConstrain better visible/ acessesible to the user.
        Overrides:
        execute in class ORMRelationCreateCommand

      • undo

        public void undo()
        This command is undone through removing the created relationshipConstrain from the source, the Model, the Relation from type relationship and the target and through deleting all the Bendpoints of the relationshipConstrain.
        Overrides:
        undo in class ORMRelationCreateCommand
